Muritala Muhammud International Airport, Lagos
The Guardian Nigeria The Nigerian Government has extended the closure of airports in the country by two weeks due to the Coronavirus pandemic. This was disclosed by the Minister of Aviation, Hadi Sirika, via his Twitter handle. However, government said emergency and essential flights could be operated from any of the airports within the period. Recall that government shut all international airports in the country on Monday, March 23, for one month.



